WorldStage Newsonline— In a bid to ensure free and fair primaries, the National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has moved  the Lagos governorship primary to October 2. The party has also rescheduled the  Enugu and Adamawa primaries to October 4. The party’s Spokesman, Mr Yekini Nabena, on Monday in Abuja said  the mode of primaries for Enugu and Adamawa states has also been changed from indirect to direct primaries.